    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="671"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4567</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-16T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Before Liberia should be asked to declare war on Germany, United States would
                    expect first that British trading vessels on <pb facs="0637" n="465"
                        xml:id="pg_465"/> coast of West Africa be permitted to resume their trade
                    with Monrovia. The Department is endeavoring to obtain assurance from British
                    Government that this will be done.</p>
                <p>Suggest to Liberian Government that it take no further action against Germany
                    until advised to do so by the Government of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
